Program: Omnibus
Title: The Dragon that Slew St George - Radioactivity
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mjt
Last Broadcast Date: 09 December 2002
In 1953 John Wayne came to St George, Utah, USA to film 'The Conqueror'. Within 20 years half of all the cast and crew developed cancer. A look at the radiation-linked illnesses caused by the effects of radioactive dust from atmospheric atomic tests in Nevada.